doc.ContractDescription: X-RAY SPECTRUM AND PULSATIONS OF THE OLD GAMMA-RAY PULSAR J1836+5925 THE BRIGHT GAMMA-RAY SOURCE 3EG J1835+5918 WAS IDENTIFIED AS A GAMMA-RAY PULSAR PSR J1836+5925 BY THE FERMI OBSERVATORY. WITH THE AGE OF 1.8 MYR, IT IS ONE OF THE OLDEST GAMMA-RAY PULSARS KNOWN. SIMILAR TO THE FAMOUS GEMINGA PULSAR, PSR J1836+5925 IS A RADIO-QUIET X-RAY SOURCE. PREVIOUS X-RAY OBSERVATIONS HAVE SHOWN THAT ITS SPECTRUM CONSISTS OF A THERMAL COMPONENT EMITTED FROM THE NEUTRON STAR SURFACE AND NONTHERMAL COMPONENT EMITTED FROM THE PULSAR MAGNETOSPHERE, BUT THEY FAILED TO DETECT ITS X-RAY PULSATIONS. WE OBSERVED PSR J1836+5925 WITH THE XMM-NEWTON OBSERVATORY IN FEBRUARY 2013 WITH THE GOAL TO DETECT ITS X-RAY PULSATIONS AND STUDY THE THERMAL AND MAGNETOSPHERIC EMISSION WITH THE AID OF ENERGY-RESOLVED TIMING AND PHASE-RESOLVED SPECTROSCOPY. OUR PRELIMINARY ANALYSIS OF THE OBSERVATIONAL DATA HAS SHOWN THAT THE OBSERVATIONS WERE QUITE SUCCESSFUL. IN PARTICULAR, THANKS TO A LOW PARTICLE BACKGROUND, WE WERE ABLE TO DETECT THE X-RAY PULSATIONS. TO COMPLETE THE ANALYSIS, THE PULSATIONS IN DIFFERENT ENERGY BANDS AND THE SPECTRA IN DIFFERENT PULSE PHASE INTERVALS MUST BE STUDIED, THE X-RAY SPECTRUM AND PULSATIONS OF THE MAGNETOSPHERIC COMPONENT MUST BE COMPARED WITH THOSE IN GAMMA-RAYS, AND THE THERMAL COMPONENT MUST BE FIT WITH REALISTIC NEUTRON STAR ATMOSPHERE MODELS. IN ADDITION, THE INFERRED PROPERTIES OF THE PSR J1836+5925 EMISSION SHOULD BE COMPARED WITH THOSE OF SIMILAR PULSARS AND WITH THE THEORETICAL MODELS. TO COMPLETE THIS WORK, WE REQUEST A SUPPORT FROM THE 2014 ADAP. THIS STUDY WILL ADDRESS THE THERMAL EVOLUTION OF NEUTRON STARS AND THE MECHANISMS OF THE PULSAR MAGNETOSPHERIC EMISSION. IT WILL ADVANCE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF GENERAL PROPERTIES AND EVOLUTION OF NEUTRON STARS, WHICH REPRESENT THE END PRODUCT OF EVOLUTION OF A SIGNIFICANT FRACTION OF STELLAR POPULATION. THE SUBJECT OF THIS PROPOSAL IS RELEVANT TO THE FOLLOWING ASTROPHYSICS STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES IN THE 2014 NASA SCIENCE PLAN: "DISCOVER HOW THE UNIVERSE WORKS, EXPLORE HOW IT BEGAN AND EVOLVED" AND "EXPLORE THE ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION OF THE GALAXIES, STARS AND PLANETS THAT MAKE UP OUR UNIVERSE".
